A DECOMPOSED and mutilated body of an unknown sangoma was found in the bushes near Sekoto River at Namahadi village in Phuthaditjhaba, Free State. Police are looking for community assistance with regard to the sangoma, who was found on 30 June by people collecting wood. A 16-year-old boy noticed a human head separated from the body when he was cutting wood near the river bank with his friends. READ: TWO recyclers shot dead at the Devland landfill site! Police spokesman Warrant officer Mmako Mophiring said the right hand had been cut loose from the body. “Other upper body parts were missing. On the right hand, the body had red, blue and white beads. It was in a state of decomposition. An inquest case has been opened,” said Mophiring. The postmortem report was expected to also reveal the gender of the deceased.